Certainly! Below is a simple C program that uses the WiringPi library to control an LED based on the state of a button connected to GPIO pin 17 (BCM GPIO 17). The LED will turn on when the button is pressed and turn off when the button is released.

First, make sure you have WiringPi installed on your Raspberry Pi. You can install it using the following commands:

```sh
