1. **Install pigpio**: If you haven't already installed the `pigpio` library, you can do so using the following commands:
   ```sh
   sudo apt-get update
   sudo apt-get install pigpiod
   ```

2. **Run pigpio daemon**: Start the `pigpio` daemon if it is not already running.
   ```sh
   sudo pigpiod
   ```

3. **Write the C program**: Create a file named `blink_led.c` and add the following code to it.

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <pigpio.h>

int main() {
    // Initialize pigpio
    if (gpioInitialise() < 0) {
        fprintf(stderr, "pigpio initialization failed\n");
        return 1;
    }

    // Set up GPIO pin 22 as an output
    gpioSetMode(22, PI_OUTPUT);

    // Infinite loop to blink the LED
    while (1) {
        // Turn the LED on
        gpioWrite(22, 1);
        // Delay for 500ms
        gpioDelay(500);

        // Turn the LED off
        gpioWrite(22, 0);
        // Delay for 500ms
        gpioDelay(500);
    }

    // This line will never be reached because of the infinite loop
    gpioTerminate();

    return 0;
}
```

4. **Compile the program**: Use the following command to compile the C program:
